item.title: My New Zealand Election 2020 Analysis
item.description: In October 2020, New Zealand held a general election. Jacinda Ardern’s Labour Party was reelected as the major governing party and, for the first time since the implementation of New Zealand’s MMP electoral system in 1996, a major party held a majority of the seats in the House of Representatives. The main opposition party, the National Party, had a catastrophic result – losing 21 seats and 18% percentage points from their 2017 result.
